Charming Californian Bungalow plus You Can Walk Everywhere!!
BURILDA A charming cottage in a fantastic walk to everything position awaits you.
Beyond the picket fence is a striking Californian Bungalow Style home, featuring 3 bedrooms, lounge , formal dining room, open plan living/meals/family area that leads you to the full length rear bi fold doors where you can sit on the deck, entertain in style and listen to all the wonderful bird life that surrounds this picture prefect property.

Gas Log Fire Places x 2

Air-conditioning

Side Access Ideal For Caravan/Trailer Storage
Outdoor Entertaining Zone
Full Rear undercover deck
Land Size 730 m2 (Approx)
This charming home is ideal for all downsizers , holiday rental or investors plus anyone looking to get out of the hustle and bustle of the city, Don't waste any time on this one as it won't be on the market long

Description:
Crown Of The Peninsula 100 Acres - 2 Titles
Superior Hilltop Property Offering Commanding Views Of Corio And Port Phillip Bays and The Bellarine Peninsula
When inspecting this magnificent property the first thing you’ll notice is the expansive, uninterrupted views of the Bays, You Yangs and surrounds from lower and upper levels. Gently undulating with rich pastures it's ideal for the horse lover or those seeking a weekend retreat and/or lifestyle change.
Easily commutable to Melbourne and offering close access to major airports, the property is positioned within the Bellarine Peninsula’s famous wine precinct and is only 20 minutes approx. to Geelong and Queenscliff (car and passenger ferry), making this quality acreage something not to be missed.
The property comprises:
. 7 fully fenced paddocks (electrified) and two holding yards
. Extensive outbuildings including 2, 4 bay machinery sheds, horse accommodation(4 loose boxes) and tack room
. Rich volcanic soil and sown pastures
. Services include: town water, power and telephone
. Comfortable 4 bedroom plus study and two living area brick home
Enquire today, inspections by appointment

Description:
Older Home - Position Perfect
When location close to all amenities in Drysdale is paramount then this property is perfect. Located in close proximity to the local early learning centre, health care professionals, cafes, shopping centre and neighbourhood centre. Park the car at home and walk to your appointments.
The home and garden are well-established and maintained and has a very homely-feel both inside and out. Perfect for your first home.
The light-filled living area is warmed by a solid fuel heater and cooled by a reverse cycle air conditioner, with a light and bright kitchen-dining area. The home has had some renovation over the years.
At the rear of the home there are three/four bedrooms and a family bathroom. The main bedroom has a semi ensuite and all have BIRs.
Outside the easy-care garden is a springtime picture. Take time to sit in the undercover outdoor entertaining area and relax.
Contact the agent to book an inspection.
Rhonda Humpage : 0457 313 609

Description:
Easy to live in, Easy to let out
Retirees'/investors delight in this impressive three bedroom home situated within the prestigious 'Bellview' complex that provides the perfect neighbourly community in a quiet, secure setting. The perfect private oasis.
Home comprises front formal lounge, tiled open plan kitchen & dining area (with additional TV point) opening out to undercover courtyard area. Well designed kitchen with island bench with breakfast bar, equipped with quality appliances including, dishwasher, gas cook-top & electric oven. Three spacious bedrooms with built in robes, master with walk in robe & ensuite.
Other features include gas ducted heating, split system air conditioning, drive through garage (5.5m x 7.5m), large clothes line, bidet (ensuite), screen door and much more.
Lovely garden aspect including two separate covered patios, a rain water tank, raised veggie bed and fruit trees.
Located across from the local recreation area within minutes to all that Drysdale has to offer.

Description:
Whats Behind The Door Will Not Disappoint!
You won't be disappointed with what you find behind this door. A true family home in every sense of the word. Kids and adults of all ages will enjoy living here. This home offers the feeling of living in a rural area, close to the Drysdale Township and on 1100 m2 (approx) this home has the lot. Indoor & outdoor living at its very best. Included are two living zones, main bedroom with ensuite and walk in robe, other 2 with BIRs. Formal lounge and a study. The 2nd living area currently boasts a large pool table for all your indoor fun but the property also has an amazing outdoor area with a European feel, imagine relaxing here. Room for the kids to kick the footy too. A larger than standard garage gives you room to move add the off street parking & this means family & friends visiting won't be an issue. The current vendors have really appreciated the proximity of this home and have many memories to take with them. It's time for someone else to appreciate this quality home.

Description:
WORK TO BE DONE
This home is what it is but the potential for this home is unmeasured. So just giving you the heads up, if you are looking for nothing to do then this place is not for you but if you are looking for a bit of a project then this property may fit the bill.
A revamp and an update will give this home a new lease of life. The main feature of this location is the views of the bay. If you removed some trees and vegetation the views from the living room would be amazing. There is a Formal dining room that could easily be used as a study. Three bedrooms all with BIR's, two bathrooms, centrally heated finished with double car port. Land size of 702m2 approx.
The current deck is need of repair which will give you opportunity to review how you want the property to look. So calling all handymen looking for a challenge let me show you around this place to get your "Block" imagination going??

Description:
Simply Stunning Elevated Home
Situated on the high side of Wintersun Court with views across Corio Bay, the You Yangs and Geelong CBD, this stylish home delivers luxury complete with an abundance of natural light and quality fixtures and fittings throughout.
Built to an exemplary level of finish, key features of this exceptional offering include a generous master bedroom with full ensuite, open plan living, dining & kitchen area which leads out through huge sliding doors to a west facing open deck area with stunning views. The kitchen is the feature of the open space with sleek modern bench tops, sleek custom made cabinetry with walk in pantry & high end appliances. The open plan living/dining area also feature wood fire place, Jarrah timber floors, ceiling fans and outstanding bay and rural views.
Downstairs offers 3 generous bedrooms with robes, main bathroom with quality tiles and fit-out, separate living area or rumpus room, laundry and access from the double remote garage. All finished off with beautiful gardens and shed for extra storage.

Description:
Charming First Home
Character, charm and a lovely country feel makes this home perfect for the first home buyer or young family looking for something just that little bit different. Boasting open-plan living downstairs with an appealing and spacious country kitchen. Polished timber floors throughout accentuate that lovely country feel to this quaint home nestled on the edge of farming hinterland.
Upstairs there are three good-sized bedrooms and the main bathroom. Views from the bedrooms scan across the roof tops to the bay and the You Yangs in the distance. Add to all this an immaculate backyard with double garage and plenty of room for a growing family and the pets. The yard is low maintenance and allows plenty of room at the rear to extend your outdoor entertaining area.
Easy access to shopping and schools by public transport. Cafes and wineries down the road.
Rhonda Humpage : 0457 313 609

Description:
CAN'T GET MUCH CLOSER!
You seriously can't get much closer to the shops and facilities at Drysdale. Everything you require to enjoy life in this lovely town is literally a very short stroll away from this Townhouse. The current Vendors have enjoyed living here and have kept the home well maintained so there is nothing to do but move in. We get many requests for townhouses/units close to amenities so I don't anticipate this one being on the market very long. Open plan kitchen, meals and lounge overlook a very pretty low maintenance garden and a nice place to sit outside undercover and read the paper with your drink of choice. Comprising two bedrooms, walk in robe in the main, built in the 2nd. Off the main living is a room currently used as a study. Remotely operated double garage with internal access. Other features include two split systems, security awnings; the toilet uses a water tank for function, solar hot water that is gas boosted. Gutter guard means never having to clean the gutters again.
I am waiting for your call to book a time to have a look.

Description:
Modern & Stylish
Set on a fully-landscaped 630m2 allotment in the heart of Drysdale, all the hard work has been done so you can simply move in and enjoy. Suited to the growing family the home offers four spacious bedrooms, the master complete with full ensuite, double shower, heated towel rail and walk-in robe, with built-in robes to the remaining bedrooms and an additional walk-in robe to the last bedroom. The gourmet kitchen is complete with stainless steel appliances, plenty of cupboard space, and faces onto on open-plan meals and living area. The additional family room is enhanced by a gas log fire to keep you warm through winter. The soaring 12ft ceilings and architectural bulk-heads are complimented by hi-lite windows and designer light fittings leading out onto a decked entertaining area that will be the setting for all those summer barbecues. Complete with ducted heating, double garage and finished in neutral tones throughout, the home is a stone's throw from shops, schools, and transport.

Description:
Fairy tale Family Home (1542m2)
Nestled in a sheltered pocket in the township of Drysdale and walking distance to all amenities, sits this lovingly restored miners cottage with a blend of classic and modern features.
Upon entering the property you are immediately wowed by the generous living area with beautiful polished floor boards, exposed brick fire place and original beams, flowing into the dining room with timber ceiling and skylight allowing plenty of natural light through.
The commercial design kitchen offers plenty of cupboard space, gas appliances, polished concrete floors and stainless steel bench tops with original beams exposed. The modern family bathroom with polished concrete floors is well laid out as well.
The 3 generous bedrooms with original features as well will be enough to make you fall in love with this home.
Set on a large block with plenty of room to extended or sub divide (STCA) backing onto nature reserve.
Other features include large lock up shed, enclosed chook pen, vegie patch and childrens pay area

Description:
Live a First Class Family Lifestyle
Presented as beautifully as a display home but with the warmth and charm that can only come from being lived in, this seven year old Hotondo built home is certainly appealing and inviting from the street but just wait until you get inside! As much as you will appreciate the rendered facade and tiered gardens with boardwalk style decking and hope that the interior will be just as attractive, what you find beyond the entry door is an exciting and unexpected surprise...
This home is HUGE!! Not only is it huge but it is also stunning! The quality of the construction is immediately evident and only continues to please as you discover all of its features. The polished timber floors in the wide entrance hall continue right through the main living area, as does the square stop cornicing. The downlighting is a feature throughout the entire house as are the top quality window furnishings. The stone accents in the family bathroom and master ensuite (with separate WC) add highlights to the neutral tonings of the home and the abundance of pot drawers in the massive kitchen (with 900mm stainless steel cooker and dishwasher) speak of the many practical considerations that have been cleverly incorporated into the design.
With 3 large living areas and 4 generous bedrooms, there is ample room here for growing families and the 720 sq m allotment allows plenty of room for both children's play as well as adult entertaining. The current owners have gone to a lot of trouble to ensure that each of these activities is just as pleasurable as the indoor living with the low maintenance gardens tiered and terraced in the back yard to provide a private, sunny decked alfresco adjacent the kitchen/meals as well as a spacious flat lawn behind the home.
Space and position have been well utilised with the elevation of the block allowing lovely valley views across to Geelong and glimpses of the bay. At night, with all of the lights twinkling, the outlook from the picture windows really comes alive. However, what lies beneath the home is just as significant a feature with three full bays of concreted storage (including a wine cellar) complete with lockable roller door and lighting. This space alone is testament to the thought, love and care that has gone into this home and proves, without a doubt that your purchase of this property will be a sound one that will provide your family with many, many years of joy.
* 720 sq m approx.
* Top Quality finish
* Large Family home
* Water Tank
* Gas Ducted Heating
* Split System Cooling/Heating
Terms: 10% deposit, balance 30/60/90/120 days
Land: 720 sq m approx.
